# .dircolors
# Used by (dircolors -b) to set the color of the ls output.
# Formatted into two columns of text, separated with whitespace.
# - The left column is file types (or extensions) in glob format.
# - The right column are the ANSI color codes for each file type.
#
# @note The first character of each line *must* be an asterisk ("*").
# Otherwise, an error is thrown on every call that requires $LS_COLORS.
# @example "*.gitignore            38;5;240"
.dircolors

